      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No, you should not take any pseudoephedrine while pregnant without first confirming it is safe with your obstetrician, as decongestants can sometimes restrict blood flow to the placenta. Please contact your doctor immediately to discuss safe alternatives like saline sprays, humidifiers, or specific steroid nasal springs approved for pregnancy that could help relieve your symptoms. Getting good rest now is crucial for both you and your baby, so remember to tell your health team exactly how severe your breathing difficulty is.",
