      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just so frustrating because i feel like i'm being told everything is a disaster over a little congestion. i've read online that some people use pseudoephedrine in the second trimester all the time and it's considered a standard treatment for sinus issues. if i just take a low dose like 30mg i can at least function. are you saying that a single low dose is actually going to cause immediate problems, or are you just being extra cautious because of the pregnancy? i really need a straight answer so i can decide what to do before my shift starts.",
